         <div rend="section">
            <head>What's the purpose?</head>
            <div rend="slide">
               <head>TEI driven slides</head>
               <p>Why do you want to do this?</p>
               <p>Because it makes your presentations reusable! 
                  You do not need to worry about proprietary formats and im- and exporting, just
                  use the <ref target="http://tei-c.org">standard for text encoding</ref> and get a true single source publishing workflow.  
               </p>
            </div>
            <div rend="slide">
               <head>A dedicated schema for slides</head>
               <p>There's a formal description of the TEI slides markup written in ODD, 
                  facilitating the authoring of the slides in your favorite (schema-aware) XML editor 
                  and making it easy for others to transform your presentations to other formats.</p>
            </div>
            <div rend="slide">
               <head>Modern web based display</head>
               <p>Using <ref target="https://github.com/TEIC/CETEIcean">CETEIcean</ref> and <ref target="https://github.com/hakimel/reveal.js">reveal.js</ref> it's simple to create beautiful online presentations from the TEI slides markup.</p>
            </div>
         </div>
         <div rend="section">
            <head>Features</head>
            <div rend="slide">
               <head>Lists</head>
               <list type="gloss">
                  <label>ordered lists</label>
                  <item>are of type <code>list rend="numbered"</code></item>
                  <label>gloss</label>
                  <item>are of type <code>list type="gloss"</code></item>
               </list>
